        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 5:09AM CDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 509 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles north of Java, or 12 miles southwest of Eureka, moving east at
40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Eureka, Hillsview, and New Town Corner.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 AM CDT for
north central South Dakota.</instruction>
